{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/punc/punc-10822/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PUNC-10822"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:08:22"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Punch-Drunk Love"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["exterior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, tracking, pan, crane, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Duration"]},"value":{"none":["long take"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man and woman talk at a restaurant."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PUNC-10822","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PUNC-10822"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1/f126b363-9f71-4f43-b57d-cb718a60b5e3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-26T20:57:44.447Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Barry responds to Lena's gratitude for his getting her out of her hotel room: “It really looks like Hawaii here.” All of Barry’s life has been mediated; he has never been on a plane. It’s no surprise then that he seems to be comparing Hawaii to all the images he has taken in of the islands. The pair have now escaped the crush and bustle of LA’s concrete, along with Barry’s sisters, and made it to a—relatively—more natural setting. It’s here that Barry and Lena can finally be alone and connect. As much as PTA’s films are love letters to his hometown, they’re not absent of critiques, both subtle and explicit, of the city. It’s nature that allows him to settle and calm his restless mind. PTA expressed a similar sentiment to Nadine Kam in an interview about the film: \"It's helpful if you're writing in a place where the wind, mountains, temperature and ocean frees you to go with their rhythm. When I'm in Hawaii, I'm in a better mind-set\" (Kam).</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10822/canvas/1#xywh=266,228,573,494"}]}]}]}